Comment: I wanted to address many of the comments Some people are complaining about the test not being fair because we ran the Note at full resolution but I m not going to gimp a phone when the galaxy phones are advertised at a specific performance spec Samsung doesn t get a free pass to advertise at one spec and get to test at a lower spec when it makes them look better The first thing I do when I get a Galaxy device is switch to standard normal full native resolution Reducing the resolution of Galaxy phones is literally putting them into power saver mode which is ridiculous since their specs are advertised as being superior to the iPhones I do mention in the video you can reduce resolution to improve battery life if you want to but you could also reduce brightness turn off wifi etc If you want to see a battery test where one of the phones is in power saver mode go watch someone else s video The funny thing is so many of internet bros are obsessed over PPI in all of my other videos They think the iPhone Xr is trash because it doesn t have PPI but the moment you run a battery test they want reduced resolution and lower PPI If Samsung wants to put in high resolution displays then they should ship their phones at the native resolution or they should ship them with a lower resolution display since all displays look crisper clearer at native res where pixels aren t shifting across one another causing fuzziness Maybe I should make a video about all of this Companies advertising higher resolution displays and then not even shipping the phones that way It s ridiculous Anyway hope you enjoyed the test See you in the next one
